12 AUTHOR: Add the following House Coauthor: Deck
13 AMENDMENT NO. 1. Strike the stricken title, enacting clause, and
entire bill and insert:
14
15 "An Act relating to Medicaid home- and community-
based services; amending 56 O.S. 2021, Section
16 1017.3, which relates to ADvantage Waiver Program;
modifying eligibility criteria; providing certain
17 exception; providing an effective date; and declaring
an emergency.
18
19
20 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
21 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 56 O.S. 2021, Section 1017.3, is
22 amended to read as follows:
23 Section 1017.3. To be eligible for the ADvantage Waiver
24 Program, a person shall:
ENGR. H. A. to ENGR. S. B. NO. 1847 Page 1

1 1. Qualify financially for Medicaid;
2 2. Be:
3 a. sixty-five (65) years of age or older, or
4 b. nineteen (19) to sixty-four (64) years of age and:
5 (1) be a physically disabled adult, as determined by
6 the Social Security Administration, age twenty-
7 one (21) years or older without
8 (2) have a developmental disability; provided, the
9 individual does not have an intellectual
10 disability or cognitive impairment related to the
11 developmental disability, or
12 (3) have a clinically documented, progressive, and
13 degenerative disease that responds to treatment
14 and previously required hospital- or long-term-
15 care-facility level of care to maintain the
16 treatment regimen to prevent health
17 deterioration;
18 3. Be determined to meet the nursing facility institutional
19 level of care by the Aging Services Division of the Department of
20 Human Services;
21 4. Reside in his or her own home or, a family member's home, or
22 an assisted living center contracted with the Department of Human
23 Services under the ADvantage Waiver Program; and
24
ENGR. H. A. to ENGR. S. B. NO. 1847 Page 2

1 5. Have needs that can be safely met with waiver services and
2 family or community supports.
3 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective July 1, 2026.
4 SECTION 3. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
5 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
6 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
7 be in full force from and after its passage and approval."
8 Passed the House of Representatives the 13th day of April, 2026.
